---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="Terms of Use">
  <div class="page-banner" style="background-image: url('/banners/about-us.jpg');">
    <h2>Terms of Use</h2>
  </div>

  <section class="section legal-section">
    <div class="legal-container">
      <p class="last-updated">Last Updated: 6th July 2026</p>

      <h3>1. Who We Are</h3>
      <p>Midnight Network ("we," "us," "our," "the Network") is a community of Discord servers and an associated website (the "Site") operated by an individual community administrator, not a registered business or legal entity. These Terms of Use ("Terms") govern your access to and use of the Site and any related bots, dashboards, and services provided by Midnight Network.</p>
      <p>By accessing or using the Site, you agree to be bound by these Terms. If you do not agree, do not use the Site.</p>

      <h3>2. Age Requirement — 18+ Only</h3>
      <p>Midnight Network, its partner servers, and the Site are intended <strong>exclusively for adults aged 18 or over</strong>. Some of our Discord servers and content contain mature, adult-oriented (NSFW) material.</p>
      <p>By using the Site or logging in via Discord OAuth, you confirm and warrant that:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>You are at least 18 years old, and</li>
        <li>You meet the minimum age of digital consent in your jurisdiction of residence.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>We do not knowingly permit access to anyone under 18. Enforcement of this requirement is carried out through these Terms and our Discord server rules rather than a technical age-verification gate. If we become aware that a user is under 18, their access will be permanently and immediately revoked across the Network, and any associated accounts or data may be removed.</p>

      <h3>3. Account Access via Discord</h3>
      <p>The Site uses <strong>Discord OAuth</strong> to authenticate users. When you log in, we receive limited information from Discord (see our <a href="/privacy-policy">Privacy Policy</a> for details). You are responsible for maintaining the security of your own Discord account. We are not responsible for any loss or damage arising from unauthorized access to your Discord account.</p>

      <h3>4. Acceptable Use</h3>
      <p>When using the Site or any Midnight Network service, you agree that you will <strong>not</strong>:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Attempt to gain unauthorized access to any part of the Site, dashboards, or bot systems;</li>
        <li>Use the Site to harass, threaten, or abuse other users or staff;</li>
        <li>Upload, submit, or transmit any content that is illegal, including but not limited to content depicting or sexualizing minors;</li>
        <li>Interfere with or disrupt the operation of the Site, bots, or connected services;</li>
        <li>Attempt to bypass, disable, or circumvent any access controls, role checks, or moderation systems;</li>
        <li>Use automated tools (bots, scrapers) to interact with the Site without our express permission;</li>
        <li>Misrepresent your identity, age, or staff/role status.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Violation of these Terms may result in removal from the Site, revocation of Discord roles, removal from partner servers, and/or a permanent ban across the Midnight Network, at our sole discretion.</p>

      <h3>5. Staff, Roles, and Dashboards</h3>
      <p>Certain areas of the Site (such as staff dashboards and bot configuration tools) are restricted to users holding specific Discord roles within Midnight Network servers, as verified through our systems. Access to these areas may be changed, revoked, or restructured at any time without notice.</p>
      <p>Staff members are additionally bound by any internal conduct policies communicated within the Midnight Staff Server, which are incorporated by reference into these Terms for staff users.</p>

      <h3>6. Content and Conduct in Partner Servers</h3>
      <p>Midnight Network's Discord servers (including but not limited to Underground Gamer Lounge, Den of Desires, Chaos Midnight House, Velvet Cozy Collar, Advertising Lounge, and Smutty Library Café) each maintain their own community rules. Continued use of the Site is contingent on compliance with those rules as well as these Terms. We reserve the right to deny or revoke Site access based on conduct in any partner server.</p>

      <h3>7. No Warranty</h3>
      <p>The Site, bots, and all related services are provided <strong>"as is" and "as available"</strong> without warranties of any kind, whether express or implied. We do not guarantee the Site will be uninterrupted, error-free, or secure, and we do not guarantee the accuracy of any data displayed (including ticket, staff, or bot configuration data).</p>

      <h3>8. Limitation of Liability</h3>
      <p>To the fullest extent permitted by law, Midnight Network and its administrators, staff, and collaborators shall not be liable for any indirect, incidental, special, or consequential damages arising from your use of, or inability to use, the Site or any related service. Midnight Network is a community project operated on a non-commercial basis; nothing in these Terms creates a liability standard beyond what is reasonable for a project of this nature.</p>

      <h3>9. Changes to These Terms</h3>
      <p>We may update these Terms from time to time. Material changes will be reflected by updating the "Last Updated" date above. Continued use of the Site after changes are posted constitutes acceptance of the revised Terms.</p>

      <h3>10. Termination</h3>
      <p>We reserve the right to suspend or terminate your access to the Site or any Midnight Network service at any time, for any reason, including violation of these Terms, without prior notice.</p>

      <h3>11. Governing Law</h3>
      <p>These Terms are governed by the laws of the United Kingdom, without regard to conflict of law principles. Any disputes arising from these Terms or use of the Site will be subject to the jurisdiction of the courts of the United Kingdom.</p>

      <h3>12. Contact</h3>
      <p>For questions about these Terms, please open a <strong>General Support</strong> ticket via the Midnight Tickets bot in the Midnight Network Discord server. If you are unable to access Discord (for example, if you have been removed from our servers), you may contact us at <a href="mailto:contact.midnightnetwork@proton.me">contact.midnightnetwork@proton.me</a>.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .page-banner {
    background-size: cover;
    background-position: center;
    height: 280px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    text-align: center;
  }
  .page-banner h2 {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    color: #F0EDF7;
    text-shadow: 0 2px 12px rgba(0,0,0,0.8);
    margin: 0;
  }
  .legal-section {
    padding-top: 3rem;
    padding-bottom: 4rem;
  }
  .legal-container {
    max-width: 780px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    text-align: left;
  }
  .last-updated {
    color: #8A7FA8;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }
  .legal-container h3 {
    color: #C4B5FD;
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    text-align: left;
    margin-top: 2.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }
  .legal-container p {
    color: #F0EDF7;
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  .legal-container ul {
    color: #F0EDF7;
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
  }
  .legal-container li {
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
  }
  .legal-container a {
    color: #8A5CF6;
    text-decoration: underline;
  }
  .legal-container a:hover {
    color: #C4B5FD;
  }
  .legal-container strong {
    color: #F0EDF7;
  }
</style>